- unique 12 byte of binary value (24 hexadecimal char)
- when we insert nay document mongodb automatically creates unique id which is called ObjectId
- 

for ex:
 await Student.create({
    title: "cpp",
    content:"pattern"
 })

stored in mongodb: 
 {
     _id: ObjectId("685fd81ad89f67b7d7e5a12"),
     title:"cpp",
     content:"pattern"
 }
